function_call.arguments: {"risks":["Lack of public awareness and political implication in disease prevention","Overreliance on scientific evidence without public awareness and political commitment","Spread of covid-19 through commuting, tourists, and businesspeople","Impact of environmental impacts on zoonosis and deforestation","Airborne virus spread in public transport","High density housing promoting contagious disease propagation","Dependence on automobiles and transportation costs","Potential aerosol transmission of respiratory diseases in indoor spaces","Impact of architectural and urban design on disease transmission","Limited methods to control bacterial pandemics before antibiotics","Inefficient traditional containment measures","Electronic dissemination may lead to widespread adoption of unverified data and methodologies, leading to incorrect public health interventions.","Dissemination of coronavirus through social contact and movement.","Failure to comply with social distancing and hygiene measures.","Misinformation leading to non-compliance with preventive measures.","No strict enforcement of covid-19 mitigation measures in the netherlands.","Inability to comply with measures due to lack of resources or knowledge.","Lack of clarity about the covid-19 measures.","Positive association between social norms and compliance","Inability to analyze changes in behavior due to single moment measurement","Data analysis on compliance measures","Low descriptive social norms for compliance with covid-19 measures"],"non-risks":["Rise in global greenhouse gas emissions","Global recession due to pandemic","Publication of non-peer reviewed research","Use of control variables","Use of stepwise regressions","Measurement of negative emotions related to covid-19 on a 7-point likert scale could lead to underreporting or misinterpretation of emotional impact."]}
